#
# Open Build Service 2.10.33
#

Please read the README.md file for initial installation
instructions or use the OBS Appliance from

  http://openbuildservice.org/download/

The dist/README.UPDATERS file has information for people updating
from a previous OBS release.

=======
Bugfixes
========

Frontend:
 * Update concurrent-ruby RubyGem to version 1.3.7
   - [GHSA-h8w8-99g7-qmvj] `AtomicReference#update` livelocks when the stored value is `Float::NAN`.
   - [GHSA-wv3x-4vxv-whpp] `ReentrantReadWriteLock` read-count overflow grants a write lock without exclusivity.
   - [GHSA-6wx8-w4f5-wwcr] ReadWriteLock allows wrong-thread write release and stray read-release counter corruption.
   - [GHSA-wv3x-4vxv-whpp] `ReentrantReadWriteLock` read-count overflow grants a write lock without exclusivity.
 * Update dalli RubyGem to version 3.2.8
   - [CVE-2022-4064] Dalli Meta Protocol request_formatter.rb self.meta_set injection.
 * Update loofah RubyGem to version 2.25.1
 * Update rails-html-sanitizer RubyGem to version 1.7.0
   - [GHSA-rxv5-gxqc-xx8g] Possible XSS vulnerability with certain configurations of rails-html-sanitizer 1.6.0.
   - [GHSA-2x5m-9ch4-qgrr] Possible XSS vulnerability with certain configurations of rails-html-sanitizer 1.6.0.
   - [GHSA-cfjx-w229-hgx5] Possible XSS vulnerability with certain configurations of rails-html-sanitizer 1.6.0.
   - [GHSA-638j-pmjw-jq48] Possible XSS vulnerability with certain configurations of rails-html-sanitizer 1.6.0.
   - [GHSA-w8gc-x259-rc7x] Possible XSS vulnerability with certain configurations of rails-html-sanitizer 1.6.0.
 * Update sprockets RubyGem to version 3.7.2
   - [CVE-2018-3760] Information leak vulnerability in Sprockets.
 * Drop peek RubyGem
 * Update yajl-ruby RubyGem to version 1.4.3
   - [GHSA-jj47-x69x-mxrm] Reallocation bug can trigger heap memory corruption.
 * Update rack RubyGem to version 2.2.23
   - [CVE-2026-34763] Root directory disclosure via unescaped regex interpolation in Rack::Directory.
   - [CVE-2026-34230] Avoid O(n^2) algorithm in Rack::Utils.select_best_encoding which could lead to denial of service.
   - [CVE-2026-26961] Raise error for multipart requests with multiple boundary parameters.
   - [CVE-2026-34786] Rack::Static header_rules bypass via URL-encoded path mismatch.
   - [CVE-2026-34831] Content-Length mismatch in Rack::Files error responses.
   - [CVE-2026-34826] Multipart byte range processing allows denial of service via excessive overlapping ranges.
   - [CVE-2026-34830] Rack::Sendfile header-based X-Accel-Mapping regex injection enables unauthorized X-Accel-Redirect.
   - [CVE-2026-34785] Rack::Static prefix matching can expose unintended files under the static root.
   - [CVE-2026-34829] Multipart parsing without Content-Length header allows unbounded chunked file uploads.
